ly</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I just don't get it...</span><hr size=1> 'Tis sorry that you werent able get your darts...maybe verant wanted to make them rare and thats why the larva are LVL 1.<br>
I love the TLC...we would have farmers everywhere without it....there is already farming going on on this server as it is...and removing TLC would increase it exponentially. <br>
<br>
Dhugal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umheddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mheddik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/24/01 6:26:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I just don't get it...</span><hr size=1> How can you even say that Verant intended to make them rare and that's why they are on L1 mobs. Remember, the TLC only exists on this server. Those larvae are L1 on *all* servers, which means they are not meant to be rare. That Vah Shir are cut off from some of their pursuits on THIS server is simply because there is no consideration of the TLC taken into account when designing new zones and new quests, so obviously we are going to have bugs/problems because of that.<br>
<br>
Face it, we are all of us on this server together a fraction of 1 percent of EQ's revenue stream. We are, ourselves, trivial. If every single one of us cancelled our accounts, they'd still be making 99.75% of the money they make now. In fact, they could turn this server into a normal server and probably make MORE money if we did that.<br>
<br>
Now that I think about it, this means that they probably won't remove TLC here to fix the bugs that exist now and crop up later because if they make it suck enough and we leave then they can divert this server's resources elsewhere and make a few extra bucks. When the population drops low enough they may just forcibly move us to standard servers and do that anyway. But definitely, no question about it, they aren't going to be devoting man hours to fixing bugs that affect such a trivial part of the population when there are probably thousands or tens of thousands of man hours still needed to fix the bugs that affect *everyone*. And by then there will be a new expansion, more bugs (especially here), and on it goes.<br>
<br>
Best bet, recruit folks to come to this server. I try to do that, here and there (but subtly, without seeming desperate), because I truly believe that if the population continues its slide we'll be moved elsewhere to allow them to better utilize resources.<br>
<br>
And you are completely wrong that I dislike the TLC because I wish to go farm some greens. I dislike it ONLY because it is buggy and it is unsupported, and I don't see how anyone rational can argue with the fact that it IS buggy and unsupported. <br>
<br>
I also disagree that you'd see farmers everywhere without it. The only 'proof' anyone has come up with for that is a comparison to normal servers, where people have disposa-chars and don't worry about reputations and far larger populations (and even there, in more than 3 years of playing, I have only had a grand total of TWO problems with farmers). That's apples and oranges. We don't have enough people to see people everywhere, for ANY reason, much less activities apt to destroy their reputations which, on a small server with one character per account, would obviously be a pretty bad idea.<br>
<br>
So the TLC pros: less farming. Well, presumably so, although there is no proof that that would be the case. That's about it for the pros, one unsubstantiated theory based on an apples-and-oranges comparison. <br>
<br>
The cons: buggy quests that are undoable or nearly undoable, for those they are intended for. No support for fixing of any related bugs. Unrealism - the mighty wizard, despite his years of mastery and massive intellect, just can't seem to figure out how to kill some things without destroying what they have despite having full access to all of his weaker spells. Reliance on the always-diminishing lower-level population of the server for completion of some quests. Lack of logic - some quests are obviously intended that YOU do them, not hire some gang of flunkies to do it. Increased reliance on spoiler sites (which is ironically the very thing that the TLC *was* intended to cut down on).<br>
<br>
I can't help but look at the pro and cons and see the cons as being FAR bigger in scope than one unproven and untested theory.<br>
<br>
But, like I said, they have no real incentive to remove the TLC. As long as we're willing to pay money to endure the inevitable bugs then they will take our money. If the population drops too low because enough people DON'T want to pay money to play on a server with an unsupported rule in the ruleset then they'll probably just move us elsewhere and make this hardware a new blue server.<br>
<br>
C'est la vie.<br>
<br>
Coriolis of Erudin, Firiona Vie, Illusionist<br>
