<br>
Now, you COULD leave it at that, but it really wouldn't be worth it.  This is a quest which evolves as you increase in skill.  First come the Xakra teeth.  Then the grimling claws.  Then the whosamawhats (forget at the moment) and finally the Owlbear feathers.<br>
<br>
This is much along the same lines as the pottery quest for the Vah Shir.  Important to note is the fact that those darts of which you speak are equippable by Vah Shir ONLY.  Therefore, if you're not a Vah Shir (dunno if you are or not) they're worthless to ya.  <br>
<br>
if you ARE a Vah Shir, then you really don't want to be messing around with them anyhow.  Each upgrade to the dart-making tool increases the quality and range of the darts.  You don't need a skill above 46 to complete the quest... just keep running through handing him his tool back (don't say it) and then taking the returned tool and the attachment and combining them in your fletching kit.<br>
<br>
