<br>
As for the 'non-role playing' argument.  Hows this:  The 'gods' of reward deem Trival combat not worth of such rewards and wisk away the desired item before the player can loot it.  Or.... Your skill and ability is so 'effective' that it destroyes the item.  Whether you 'choose' to accept either RP explaination is a moot issue. What is fact is that the TLC can simply be explained in a 'RP' themology, and thus is not 'anti-RP'.  Just because you don't like something does not mean it is always OOC or 'anti-RP'.<br>
<br>
